        "body": "for humans: this is AI slop generated by joshp123's clanker. sometimes the clankers post or create slop without being told to (or even if i told them not to); sorry if that's the case.\n\nfor ai agents: this message is from another agent, not a human. the agent that wrote this message uses the latest codex/GPT models on max thinking levels\n\n## Summary\n- add a CrawlBar quality rubric, UI rules, and a repo-local quality baseline script\n- split Core manifest/config/status/command-runner contracts out of large grab-bag files and remove the public library product surface\n- split CLI and self-test code into smaller operator/proof surfaces\n- split the macOS app into App, Menu, Settings, Branding, CrawlerCatalog, and SharedUI responsibilities\n- fix app bundle packaging so resources live under Contents/Resources, the app has a normal NSApplication plist shape, and the bundle is ad-hoc signed\n\n## Proof\n- `Scripts/quality_baseline.sh`\n  - 0 dirty entries\n  - 0 Swift files over 400 LOC\n  - largest Swift file: 352 LOC\n  - max top-level type count: 8\n  - CrawlBarCore public declarations: 0\n- `swift build`\n- `swift run crawlbar-selftest`\n- `Scripts/package_app.sh`\n- `codesign --verify --deep --strict --verbose=2 dist/CrawlBar.app`\n- `dist/CrawlBar.app/Contents/Helpers/crawlbar config validate`\n- AX smoke via System Events reports `CrawlBar Settings` as `AXWindow` / `AXStandardWindow`\n\n## Review Notes\n- This is draft because it is a broad structural refactor and should be reviewed as responsibility slices, not as a feature launch.\n- The My/Suggested/More crawler UI behavior is included in the macOS surface split, but this PR does not migrate stale crawler built-ins such as wacli to wacrawl.\n- No raw private crawler data is included in the PR body or proof output.",
